Item [26] promotes Maca Yeast. Includes recipes for breads, rolls, coffee cakes,
                and root beer; offers for stamp collection stamp album and booklets about stamps;
                address of Hannah L. Wessling to whom questions about Maca Yeast may be sent;
                illustrations of period dress, serving suggestions, and product packaging; and
                index. Sample recipes: prune bread, 60-minute Parker House rolls, and Scandinavian
                Christmas bread. Damaged: cover torn.

Item [36] is a catalog for Well-Bred Loaf's baked goods. Includes list of products
                with prices and shipping costs; details of how to order by mail or telephone;
                suggestions of occasions for using products; and history of company. No recipes.

Item [15] promotes Occident Flour. Includes baking hints, measurements, score card
                for judging, and white sauce hints. Sample recipes: basic recipe for biscuit dough,
                raisin rolls, and steamed brown bread. Marked D 12.

Item [9] was published by General Foods to provide information for economic and
                nutritious food preparation during wartime rationing. Includes foreword from Betty
                Crocker on women's roles as soldiers, in home defense, and making do with less;
                methods, recipes, and menus to extend rationed foods; nutrition information;
                advertisement for Softasilk cake-making methods; sample social events for wartime;
                product packaging illustrations; and index, Some sections use include poems and
                military language. Sample recipes: pinwheel meat roll, mock Indian pudding, war-time
                cake, service cake, and plentiful pot pie. Some loose pages.

Item [12] promotes Gold Medal flour. Includes serving suggestion illustrations;
                testimonial with illustration from Barbara Reid Robson, home economics consultant;
                and offer for Betty Crocker party favors. Notes flour is now "enriched in the
                interests of public health in connection with the National Defense Program." Series
                7 ; 1. Sample recipes: French apple pie and graham gems. 2 copies.

Item [5] is similar to item [4] but includes special offer of baking ware;
                comparison recipes using bread flour and Swan's Down flour; cover illustration of
                swans.

Item [9] contains essay by Frances Lee Barton; specifies "all measures are level";
                includes recipe for Japanese skillet cake, Genoese Cake; offers for cake set, oven
                thermometer; back cover has illustration of decorated cup cakes.

Item [26] includes Army and Navy regulations for sending packages to servicemen;
                recipes for cakes and cookies suitable for shipping; recipes similar to item [23];
                cover portrait of Kate Smith.

Item [27] is similar to item [23], except includes recipes for "Fluffy Frostings";
                directions for using mixer for recipes, illustrations of mixer inside and on front
                and back covers.

Item [1] includes recipes for Welsh rarebit, sponge balls for soup, and shrimp
                wiggle; bread recipes with quantities for dried, compressed, and home-made yeast;
                table of times, weights, and measures; specification of level measures in recipes;
                mention of steel roller milling and Hungarian gradual reduction process; back cover
                illustration of mill; and history of mill.

Item [28] promotes Jiffy mixes. Includes inside front cover illustration of mill;
                back cover illustrations of product packages. Recipes for carrot bread, grasshopper
                pie with liquor, chocolate fondue, and pizza.
